    "username": "emollick",
    "nickname": "Ethan Mollick",
    "text": "Unappreciated fact is the second scaling law does not seem to completely plateau in many tasks: throw more tokens at a reasoning AI model and get better answers, especially with a simple harness.\n\nBenchmark performance is actually limited by token usage. https://t.co/jP3TgIsT2T https://t.co/DQs6OJvNTy",
    "quoted_tweet": null,
    "url": "https://twitter.com/emollick/status/2040911007392903231",
    "time": "2026-04-06 05:54",
    "id_str": "2040911007392903231",
    "is_retweet": false
  },
  {
    "username": "emollick",
    "nickname": "Ethan Mollick",
    "text": "Real world example: raising token limits from 3M to 10M tripled the amount of work that Codex could do independently on cybersecurity tasks. From 3.1 hours to 10.5 hours.",
    "quoted_tweet": null,
    "url": "https://twitter.com/emollick/status/2040912749849432258",
    "time": "2026-04-06 06:01",
    "id_str": "2040912749849432258",
    "is_retweet": false
  },
  {
    "username": "emollick",
    "nickname": "Ethan Mollick",
    "text": "I am impressed by Gemma 4, there’s a lot of power for an on-device model at fast speeds. But I am not convinced you can get real agentic workflows out of a small model on device. So much depends on model judgement, self-correction, and accuracy. Small models are too weak there. https://t.co/Adi9vlYL24",
    "quoted_tweet": null,
    "url": "https://twitter.com/emollick/status/2040925197767762425",
    "time": "2026-04-06 06:51",
    "id_str": "2040925197767762425",
    "is_retweet": false
  },
  {
    "username": "emollick",
    "nickname": "Ethan Mollick",
    "text": "Diagrams from here: https://t.co/D557qQbs5g\n\nThe Apple bet appears to be they can pull this all off with on-device models. Really not sure that is the case. There is a reason agentic workflows only took off with recent frontier models. We shall see.",
    "quoted_tweet": null,
    "url": "https://twitter.com/emollick/status/2040925705836405097",
    "time": "2026-04-06 06:53",
    "id_str": "2040925705836405097",
    "is_retweet": false
  },
